author: Sam J.
title: WTF is a SUPER-precedent!? Gorsuch makes Dianne Feinstein look like a twit over Roe v Wade [video]
text:
Could he make Dianne look any dumber? He didn’t even have to try. @cspan @SenFeinstein : "Super-precedent" is that like double secret probation? 
— The Right Wing M (@TheRightWingM)   AWESOME: Judge Gorsuch cites Charlie Brown in Senate   

Dianne is trying to make Roe v Wade some super law that if confirmed, Gorsuch wouldn’t be able to overturn. Of course she’s absolutely wrong but hey, whatever helps her sleep at night. @cspan @SenFeinstein to Gorsuch: Abortion is "Super-duper precedent" but Freedom to Exercise Religion & Right to Bear Arms must be curtailed 
— The Right Wing M (@TheRightWingM) March 21, 2017 
SUPER-DUPER law. 
— AD (@BigWavis) March 21, 2017 
Not so much painful – we got a YUGE laugh out of it. @cspan Who told her to say super precedent? Her staffers and handlers may be the worst in DC 
— Joe Riordan (@JMM30225) March 21, 2017 
Betting no one told her to say ‘super-precedent,’ she’s just not that bright and thought it would make Roe v Wade sound more important or something. @cspan @SenFeinstein super precedent? Is that a legal term? This woman is in way over her head 
— Tommy Hogan (@Hogantommyhogan) March 21, 2017 
What’s even funnier is we found this footage retweeted on HER timeline, like she is proud of how she asked this question. 
Heh.
